# Boss Slicer SL-2 

The Boss Slicer SL-2 can be connected to a PC via USB. The Boss Tone Studio software can then be used to import and export collections of patterns called Live Sets as .tsl files. At the time of writing Boss have not provided a pattern editor. 

# Live set TSL files
The .tsl files use the JSON file format and contain:

* Header info
  * name: Preset Patches
  * formatRev: 0001
  * device: SL-2  
*  Data array: A data array consisting of up to 88 elements each representing a single pattern (8 types, 11 variations). Each pattern consists of a memo and a paramSet.
   * memo: null
   * isToneCentralPatch: true - this value is set to true even for third-party livesets (e.g. McRocklin's).
   * paramSet: The paramSet consists of 17 elements which themselves seem to contain Hex named PATCH%<Name>. I suspect that the parameters with names ending "(1)" and "(2)" indicate left and right output channels.

The [Boss MD-500 Owner's Manual](https://static.roland.com/assets/media/pdf/MD-500_eng01_W.pdf) provides a useful reference for decoding what individual paramSet values represent.
